CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 30, 1958, pg. 32 reads: " Stands Alone - Pittsburgh has numerous male golfers, but it was apparent this week that the fairway game hasn't made a deep impression upon female golfers in this area. Of the 65 women taking part in UGA golf tournament, only one Pittsburgher, Mrs. Kathleen Fitts, above, is listed as a participant."
TitMainTitle: Kathleen Fitts wearing dark buttoned down skirt with chain belt, short sleeved gingham blouse, and two toned shoes, putting golf ball for UGA tournament at North Park
